sentences: He attended Francis Scott Key High School before moving on to the University of South Florida, on a swimming scholarship, where he earned a BFA in music composition in 1979.
In 1988, he joined Elton John's studio and touring band, appearing on the album Sleeping with the Past.
In 1990, he performed with the group Warpipes, a side project of fellow Elton John member Davey Johnstone.
In 2001, Babylon won a Grammy Award for his contributions on the Elton John / Tim Rice musical Aida.
He died of a heart attack on September 2, 2009, after swimming in a pool.
Guy's page on Vimeo (includes one video, "Las Vegas Twister", which he produced and uploaded in 2009 shortly before his death)
